BFN 

  [Text] Austria has protested to Belgrade over the temporary 
arrest of ORF correspondent Veronika Seyr in Pale near Sarajevo. 
Foreign Minister Alois Mock summoned the Belgrade charge 
d'affaires to the Foreign Ministry and protested against the 
suppression of reporting. In addition, Austria has asked the 
CSCE to intervene. The International Press Institute has 
supported the protest. Seyr's report on the situation in 
Gorazde and all the equipment that she was carrying were seized 
by Serbian troops yesterday. She herself was questioned for 
several hours. 

